    "Id": "vehiclechassisdef_LONGTOM-LT-MOB-25",
    "Name": "Long Tom LT-MOB-25",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Mobile Long Tom Artillery LT-MOB-25</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Standard </color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>4/7 (Tracked)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>225 ICE</color></b>\n\nThe Mobile Long Tom, a heavy artillery vehicle, is a massive convoy of six vehicles. The main unit is a 65-ton tracked vehicle that includes a pair of 5-ton support carriages, followed by three 10-ton ammunition carriages. Each vehicle has only two tons of armor, but the LT-MOB-25 is not meant to be anywhere near combat. For this reason, it relies on defensive units for anti-air support.\n\nThe purpose of this entire convoy is to move a single weapon: a Long Tom Rifle Mobile Chassis System. The artillery piece is capable of extremely long-range fire, making it ideal for demolishing defensive fortifications rather than engaging mobile targets. The only short-range weapons are four side-mounted Machine Guns, which are more suited for anti-infantry defense.",
